(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An evil result:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*aAquwA Halaba A^amorihimo", "text_ar": "ذَاقُوا حَلَبَ اَمْرِهِمْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They tasted the evil result of their affair,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "action"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA lahu laA HalabN", "text_ar": "مَا لَهُ لَا حَلَبٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "walaA jalabN", "text_ar": "وَلَا جَلَبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", mentioned by IAar, but not explained by him, (TA,) is said to be a form of imprecation [meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What aileth him? May he have neither she-camels nor he-camels"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (K;) and this is the opinion generally held: (TA:) but some say that there is no reason for this [assertion; holding the meaning to be,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he has neither she-camels nor hecamels;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the former"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lA", "text_ar": "لا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being redundant: see 4; and see also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jalabu", "text_ar": "جَلَبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (K.)       -A2-  Also The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "covering, exterior part, peel,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qi$or", "text_ar": "قِشْر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) of anything. (Kr, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "A", "S", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n8792", "headword_ar": "حُلُبٌ", "root": "Hlb", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "[a pl. of which the sing. is not mentioned,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Black;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as applied to animals. (K. [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HulobuwbN", "text_ar": "حُلْبُوبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Intelligent;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as applied to men. (K.)"}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n8810", "headword_ar": "حُلَّبٌ", "root": "Hlb", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain plant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that grows in the hot season, in the plains and on the sides of valleys, cleaving to the ground so as almost to be buried in it, not eaten by the camels, but only by the sheep"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goats,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and by the gazelles:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it increases the milk, and fattens; and gazelles are snared"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "while pasturing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tHtbl ElyhA", "text_ar": "تحتبل عليها"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "): (TA:) hence the expressions"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tayosu AlHul~abi", "text_ar": "تَيْسُ الحُلَّبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tayosN *uw Hul~abK", "text_ar": "تَيْسٌ ذُو حُلَّبٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a buck-gazelle that feeds upon the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hl~b", "text_ar": "حلّب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is a curling herb, of a dusty colour inclining to green, that spreads upon the ground; when a piece of it is cut off, a milky fluid flows from it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S:) AHn says,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is a plant that spreads upon the ground, evergreen, having small leaves, with which they tan:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "Aboo-Ziyád says,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is included among what are termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alxilofap", "text_ar": "الخِلْفَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and is a tree that expands over the ground, cleaving thereto, intensely green, growing most when the heat becomes great:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and he adds, on the authority of Arabs of the desert, that"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it lies upon the ground, having small and bitter leaves, and a root penetrating deep into the earth, and small twigs: it is of the kind of plants termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ray~iHapN", "text_ar": "رَيِّحَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "K", "TA", "As"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}